that asks for an email address, I use thier email address.  I relise that that would be an unethical thing to do.  But would it work?   When their emails became unusable because of all the going bald, viagra pills, britny spears nude, and lowest morgage rate emails, would it be worth it to get some spam laws on the books?<br><br>How bad is your spam problem? <p><center><a href=http://www.drugwarfacts.org>Drug War Facts</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufulseman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fulseman</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/10/02 4:52:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxenix1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xenix1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 2225<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/4/02 11:23:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1117.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An idea to stop spam.</span><hr size=1> ahahahaha<br>dude thats hillarious, and it would WORK except im assumeing those email accts have a nice filter program running to get rid of the spam <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Signatures are the devil!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaruvius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aruvius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/4/02 11:27:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1117.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><